SIMPLE: generalship
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Generalship
<hw>Gen"er*al*ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The office of a
general; the exercise of the functions of a general; -- sometimes, with
the possessive pronoun, the personality of a general.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your <qex>generalship</qex> puts me in mind of Prince Eugene.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Military skill in a general officer or
commander.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Fig.: Leadership; management.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An artful stroke of <qex>generalship</qex> in Trim to raise a
dust.</q> <rj><qau>Sterne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Generalty</ent>⟦br⟧
